What does this program print?

```cpp
#include <iostream>
void addFive(int* p) { *p += 5; }
int main() {
    int n { 3 };
    addFive(&n);
    std::cout << n << '\n';
    return 0;
}
```

This code compiles and runs but prints a memory address instead of the integer value. What is the bug?

```cpp
#include <iostream>
